    • onFilterApplied

      void onFilterApplied(String timeFilter, boolean isHappy, boolean isSad, boolean isAngry, boolean isSurprised, boolean isAfraid, boolean isDisgusted, boolean isConfused, boolean isShameful)
      Called immediately when the user applies filters.
      Parameters:
      timeFilter - The time filter string (e.g., "last_24_hours", "3Days", "last_week", "last_month", or "all_time").
      isHappy - True if "Happy" is selected.
      isSad - True if "Sad" is selected.
      isAngry - True if "Angry" is selected.
      isSurprised - True if "Surprised" is selected.
      isAfraid - True if "Afraid" is selected.
      isDisgusted - True if "Disgusted" is selected.
      isConfused - True if "Confused" is selected.
      isShameful - True if "Shameful" is selected.

    • onFilteredResults

      void onFilteredResults(List<MoodEvent> results)
      Called after Firestore fetching and filtering is complete.
      Parameters:
      results - The final list of filtered MoodEvent objects.
